ZCZC EE82
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 202300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A MOD TO STRG SE FLOW LIES ACROSS THE N SEA WITH A
BROAD RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LYING ACROSS SCANDINAVIA AND LOW PRESSURE IN
THE EERN ATLANTIC JUST W OF IRELAND. A FURTHER LOW LIES IN FITZROY. BOTH
THE HIGH AND LOW STAY SLOW MOV THROUGH INTO TUESDAY MORNING. LATER TUESDAY
AND THROUGH WEDNESDAY A DPN LOW IN BISCAY PUSHES FRONTAL TROUGHS N ACROSS
THE CHANNEL AND THEN NWARDS ACROSS THE UK BRINGING THUNDERY CONDITIONS.
FURTHER THUNDERY SHWRS ARE THEN LIKELY ON THURSDAY AS DPN ATLANTIC LOWS PUSH
E INTO THE W OF IRELAND. MONDAY EVENING GALES ARE POSS IN FITZROY CONTINUING
INTO TUESDAY GRADUALLY EASING BY THE END OF THE DAY. FURTHER GALES THEN
DEVELOPING FITZROY THROUGH WEDNESDAY AND INTO THURSDAY. THESE SPREADING N
THROUGH THURSDAY TO AFFECT SOLE AND PERHAPS SHANNON BY THE EVENING
